
[1]beatifical

   BEATIF'ICAL, a. [L. beatus, blessed, from beo, to bless, and facio, to
   make. See Beatify.]

   That has the power to bless or make happy, or the power to complete
   blissful enjoyment; used only of heavenly fruition after death; as
   beatific vision.
